Recap :
Components : Nothing but function which return JSX - Reusable HTML components . 


Props - every components are like function . function has parameters. components has props 
 
--------------------------------------------------------

import axios from "axios"
function App() {
  let data = [] ;
  axios.get("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos")
    .then(response => {
      data = response.data;
    })
  return (
    <>
      <div className="">

        {
          JSON.stringify(data)
        }</div></>
  )
}

export default App

this wont show anything since the initially the data is empty and after even feting the DOM is not updated

IMPORTANT - 1. React only rerenders componets if a "State variable" changes 
Rerendering - ? 
- In non react world -  DOM manipulation  
- IN react world u are not expected to write DOM manipulation u are expected to just update the state variables and react will update the DOM manipulation/

State Variables -
Not every variable is a state variable. 
U have to tell react specifically the given variable is  a state variable. then only react will rerender. 

let [data, setData] = useState([]);
useState([]) // has 2 values [a,b]
a = data , b = set Data ; hence u destructure it  [data, setData] 

other wise 
let returnValue = useState([]);//[a,b] 
const date = returnValue[0] ; //current Value 
const setData = returnValue[1];  

useState is also a function but is called as Hook just like componenet is a function but is called as Component. 

easier syntax :
let [data, setData] = useState([]);


Foreach Vs Map 
Foreach when u want to run some logic on array of elements
Map is when u want to transform array of something into array of something => returns new Array

If u keep 
 // axios.get("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos")
  //   .then(response => {
  //     setData(response.data);
  //   }) 
   this you will observe 2 things :
   1. APP components gets render infinitely if u log u can check that.
   2. Infine request to JSON placeholder API . 

   Now why this ?  
   upuntill we understood,
   UseState  - 1. data - current Value 2. setData - function to update data 

   Whenever state variable changes react "rerenders" . Now what is this rerender ? 
   Rerender - someone again call APP();
   hence what again happens is again request goes state variable updates component loads again request goes and cycle continues.


useEffect - lets u run side effect. SIdeeffect - outside component renderCycle
Use Effect takes teo arguments a function and a array ;
function - whatever written in function is now gurded from componnents rerender cycle.
if dependency array is empty . 

useEffect(function(){
 
},[]);

with Empty dependency array :
this function will only run on the first render - mount 

useEffect(function(){
 axios.get("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos")
    .then(response => {
       setData(response.data);
     }) 
},[]);


useEffect also return a  function it is  a cleanup function 
it runs with old data and then sideeffect function runs 




